1
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:02,520
Oh my goodness.

2
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:03,640
You scared me.

3
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,120
What are you daydreaming about?

4
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:07,359
Hold it tight.

5
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:09,840
Don't get it dirty.

6
00:01:10,439 --> 00:01:11,560
I designed it myself.

7
00:01:12,079 --> 00:01:14,000
I thought you were as clumsy as you are.

8
00:01:14,519 --> 00:01:15,400
If you're so worried,

9
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:16,879
come to the wedding site and watch it.

10
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,400
I'd love to,

11
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,200
but I'm too busy with business.

12
00:01:20,519 --> 00:01:21,640
I have to go back to Korea next week.

13
00:01:22,319 --> 00:01:24,599
No wonder you're so upset.

14
00:01:25,239 --> 00:01:26,000
If you're leaving,

15
00:01:27,239 --> 00:01:28,359
who are you reluctant to part with?

16
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,200
Lin Hao.

17
00:01:30,959 --> 00:01:31,480
Are you satisfied now?

18
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:32,040
Yes.

19
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:34,040
Then why are you still standing there?

20
00:01:34,159 --> 00:01:35,120
Where are we going?

21
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,760
What are we pushing?

22
00:01:36,959 --> 00:01:38,079
I've tried everything.

23
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:40,120
But this pushing doesn't work at all.

24
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:41,680
Oh my god.

25
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,319
I'm telling you,

26
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,319
if you want to be sincere,

27
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:49,040
Yunfei's sincerity works well on me.

28
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,799
Don't be so complacent.

29
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,599
My brother has tried many tricks on you.

30
00:01:53,319 --> 00:01:55,000
I don't care if he has tried tricks or not.

31
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,719
If you don't seize the opportunity now,

32
00:01:57,159 --> 00:01:58,400
don't wait until you go back to South Korea,

33
00:01:58,519 --> 00:01:59,959
and cry at midnight while eating pickles.

34
00:02:00,159 --> 00:02:01,959
You are the one who will cry at midnight while eating pickles.

35
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:02,920
That's right.

36
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,000
That's the spirit.

37
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,359
Do you dare to ask him

38
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,560
like this one more time?

39
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:07,560
Yes.

40
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:09,759
I dare.

41
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:10,759
OK.

42
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:12,919
Run, Ma.

43
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:15,759
Go.

44
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:16,840
Lan Xiaochuan.

45
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:22,159
I'll go.

46
00:02:23,439 --> 00:02:24,400
I dare.

47
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:46,879
Auntie Du.

48
00:02:48,039 --> 00:02:49,159
How do you want to take the wedding photos?

49
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,240
Whatever you want.

50
00:02:58,960 --> 00:02:59,639
Why are you here?

51
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:01,879
Isn't Auntie Du going to take wedding photos?

52
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:04,560
Take mine first to practice.

53
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,360
Brother.

54
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:07,719
Stop it.

55
00:03:08,759 --> 00:03:09,439
Honey.

56
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:13,400
I don't even have a wedding photo.

57
00:03:14,039 --> 00:03:15,840
I feel so wronged.

58
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,680
Just take two for me.

59
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,639
I won't go out to take photos.

60
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,520
I'm saving you money.

61
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,599
What a lousy guy!

62
00:03:25,759 --> 00:03:26,759
His wife is so pretty,

63
00:03:26,919 --> 00:03:28,000
yet he's so stingy!

64
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:32,400
Honey.

65
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:33,879
Honey, honey.

66
00:03:34,039 --> 00:03:34,800
Don't, honey.

67
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,800
Don't shout.

68
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,000
It's nostalgic, right?

69
00:03:59,039 --> 00:03:59,759
Jin Caien,

70
00:04:02,319 --> 00:04:03,439
can you be more mature?

71
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,479
That's not how you joke around.

72
00:04:11,039 --> 00:04:11,879
Stop right there!

73
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:18,000
You just left like that.

74
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,519
Who do you think you are?

75
00:04:20,199 --> 00:04:21,240
I waited for you for three years.

76
00:04:22,279 --> 00:04:23,519
You never even looked for me.

77
00:04:25,079 --> 00:04:26,000
Am I

78
00:04:26,519 --> 00:04:27,759
that unappealing to you?

79
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,199
Back then,

80
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,199
why did you break up with me so easily?

81
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,399
You said you didn't want a long-distance relationship,

82
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,000
and that was it.

83
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,040
Why did we break up?

84
00:04:44,399 --> 00:04:45,279
You owe me an explanation.

85
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:50,399
Fine.

86
00:04:53,759 --> 00:04:55,040
Let's get this straight today.

87
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,959
President, thank you.

88
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:12,319
Cai En,

89
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,160
is this your boyfriend?

90
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,879
Yes, he's Chinese.

91
00:05:17,319 --> 00:05:18,879
He looks pretty average.

92
00:05:30,639 --> 00:05:32,519
He can't understand us, can he?

93
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:37,600
He doesn't speak Korean.

94
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:44,000
Actually, I understood everything

95
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:44,879
you said that day.

96
00:05:46,319 --> 00:05:47,519
You said you wanted to stay in Seoul,

97
00:05:48,519 --> 00:05:49,319
so I learned Korean

98
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,519
and planned to settle there.

99
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,560
I should have learned slower,

100
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:59,160
then I wouldn't have understood.

101
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,639
Why didn't you say anything sooner?

102
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,439
I didn't know what to say.

103
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,120
There was no room for discussion at that time.

104
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,439
This is why we broke up?

105
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:12,759
My dad clearly gave the ring to auntie.

106
00:07:13,639 --> 00:07:15,000
How could it be missing?

107
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,959
Where could it be?

108
00:07:20,759 --> 00:07:23,360
If I had known, I wouldn't have said it was a prop ring.

109
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:24,839
It's not here, either.

110
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,439
Maybe we should look for it another day.

111
00:07:28,879 --> 00:07:29,480
No.

112
00:07:29,879 --> 00:07:30,879
You gave it to me.

113
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:31,959
We have to find it.

114
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:41,639
Lan Xiaochuan,

115
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,519
how about we hold the wedding

116
00:07:47,199 --> 00:07:48,199
together?

117
00:07:50,519 --> 00:07:51,600
What are you talking about?

118
00:07:52,759 --> 00:07:54,240
How can we hold the wedding together?

119
00:07:54,639 --> 00:07:55,800
That's hilarious.

120
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:01,360
What was that just now?

121
00:08:02,439 --> 00:08:03,439
Proposing to me?

122
00:08:12,399 --> 00:08:13,000
Found it.

123
00:08:14,639 --> 00:08:15,360
Let me see.

124
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:36,799
Give it to me.

125
00:08:49,879 --> 00:08:51,080
You're lying to me.

126
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,559
Then I'll lie to you again.

127
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:14,440
Order dinner yourselves.

128
00:09:14,919 --> 00:09:15,960
I'm going out.

129
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:21,480
Okay, ma'am.

130
00:09:27,759 --> 00:09:28,240
Mom.

131
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:30,960
Xiaochuan.

132
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,279
Xiaochuan has something to tell you.

133
00:09:33,039 --> 00:09:33,679
What's up?

134
00:09:34,679 --> 00:09:35,360
Nothing.

135
00:09:35,679 --> 00:09:36,720
That prop ring

136
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:37,919
was a gift for Xiaochuan.

137
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,360
She wants to know where you put it.

138
00:09:44,279 --> 00:09:46,039
Well, you order something.

139
00:09:46,559 --> 00:09:47,919
Order Xiaochuan's favorite food.

140
00:09:52,919 --> 00:09:54,480
Is there something you need?

141
00:10:00,639 --> 00:10:01,960
Don't just stand there.

142
00:10:02,679 --> 00:10:03,279
Come over here.

143
00:10:03,519 --> 00:10:04,120
Let's talk.

144
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:04,919
No, no, no.

145
00:10:05,159 --> 00:10:07,320
I'm fine here.

146
00:10:07,639 --> 00:10:08,600
Don't worry,

147
00:10:08,759 --> 00:10:10,039
we're civilized people.

148
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:11,559
We won't hit you.

149
00:10:12,519 --> 00:10:13,279
Yes, yes.

150
00:10:14,519 --> 00:10:15,879
Boss Liu, please,

151
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,120
can you give me a couple more days?

152
00:10:18,679 --> 00:10:20,759
My brother-in-law is getting married soon.

153
00:10:20,879 --> 00:10:22,919
He must have received a lot of gifts.

154
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:24,840
Your brother-in-law?

155
00:10:25,879 --> 00:10:26,919
The woman he's marrying,

156
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,159
her name is Du Juan, right?

157
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:29,240
That woman

158
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:31,240
is heavily in debt herself.

159
00:10:31,879 --> 00:10:34,639
Your brother-in-law has the money but doesn't help her pay it off.

160
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:36,360
Why would he give it to you?

161
00:10:36,679 --> 00:10:37,600
You...

162
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:38,320
Who are you talking about?

163
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:41,000
Is Du Juan in debt?

164
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:43,120
What do you think?
